cas:Sofa.sofaString: Progress Notes - 06/20/2013 Return to TOC Patient: DOB: Date: 06/20/2013 14:00 Provider: Encounter: Return Visit ACTIVE PROBLEMS - Degeneration lumbar disc " Low Back Pain * Lumbar radiculopathy - right - Lumbar Spondylosis - Morbid Obesity - Osteoarthritis Knee - right - Pes Anserine Bursitis - right - Spinal stenosis lumbar region - Subdeltoid Bursitis - bilateral - Trochanteric bursitis - right CHIEF COMPLAINT The Chief Complaint is: Low back and right lower extremity pain. HISTORY OF PRESENT ILLNESS is a 43 year old female. - Medication list reviewed. - Patient is experiencing the most pain in the the low back and right lower extremity The above has been an a major problem for over 3 years - The pain is getting worse - Patient has morning stiffness that lasts for all day - Able to dress self with much difficulty or with assistance - Able to get in and out of bed with some difficulty * Able to lift full cup or glass to mouth without difficulty - Able to walk outdoors on flat ground with some difficulty - Able to wash and dry entire body with some difficulty - Able to bend down and pick up clothing with much difficulty or with assistance Able to turn taps on and off without difficulty - Able to get in and out of car with some difficulty She continues to be most bothered by low back and right lower extremity pain. She also notes intermittent right lower extremity paresthesia. She is seeing a pain specialist at Baystate Medical Center and has been diagnosed with right lower extremity radiculopathy. She's had several lumbar corticosteroid injections with no lasting benefit. She states that lumbar surgery is being considered. Her low back and right lower extremity pain tend to be worse during weight bearing activities with twisting and bending of her spine. She denies left lower extremity pain or paresthesia. She denies bowel or bladder dysfunction. She also complains of less bothersome intermittent pain involving her shoulders, right hip and right knee. She denies joint swelling but experiences "all day" stiffness. Her medications provide only modest benefit and her well-tolerated. Physical therapy and several other medications in the past been ineffective. CURRENT MEDICATION - Advair Diskus 250-50 MCG/DOSE AEPB, twice a day, 0 days, 0 refills - Ambien 10 MG TABS, , 0 days, 0 refills, hs - Amitriptyline HCI 100 MG TABS, , 0 days, 0 refills, 1 tab po at hs.
